article.description: Julie Wojta scored 15 points in 25 minutes and Adrian Ritchie had nine points and eight rebounds as No. 18 Green Bay rolled to a 76-49 victory over Loyola of Chicago on Saturday.
article.headline: Julie Wojta, No. 14 Green Bay handle Loyola of Chicago
article.linkText: No. 14 Green Bay rolls behind Wojta's 15 points
article.story:
GREEN BAY, Wis. --  Julie Wojta scored 15 points in 25 minutes and Adrian Ritchie had nine points and eight rebounds as Green Bay (No. 14 ESPN/USA Today, No. 18 AP) rolled to a 76-49 victory over Loyola of Chicago on Saturday.

Wojta also eight rebounds, four assists and four steals for the Phoenix (12-0, 2-0 Horizon League). Ritchie had six assists. Green Bay held the Ramblers (6-7, 1-1) to 37.5 percent shooting and forced 34 turnovers to extend its winning streak to 28 games against conference foes.

Green Bay trailed 10-8 before a 14-0 run over 5 minutes, 49 seconds. The spurt was highlighted by an entry pass inside to Wojta, whose tip pass to the wing set up an uncontested 3-pointer by Ritchie. Later in the half, Green Bay held the Ramblers without a basket for 5:02 as it built a 45-24 halftime.

Simone Law and Abby Skube scored 10 points apiece for Loyola.
